CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 16, 1962, pg. 23 reads: "Tabulating Scores - Members of the Alpha Wives are busily tabulating the scores of players at their annual bridge luncheon, which took place Saturday at Hotel Webster Hall.  Left to right, seated: Mmes. Franklin E. Bolden, George W. Little, Wendell G. Freeland, Frederick S. Humphries, LeRoy Patrick, Wilbur C. Douglass Sr. and Robert L. Vann.  Standing; Mmes, Larry Green, John Cundieff, Lawrence Moncrief, Richard S. Bennett, Wilbur Douglass Jr., Edward Hale, Robert Lawson, James Miller and John Walker. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Alpha Phi Alpha wives, seated from left: Helen Bolden, Mrs. George W. Little, Mrs. Wendell G. Freeland, Mrs. Frederick S. Humphries, Mrs. LeRoy Patrick, Mrs. Wilbur C. Douglass, and Jessie Vann; standing: Mrs. Larry Green, Mrs. John Cundieff, Mrs. Lawrence Moncrief, Mrs. Richard S. Bennett, Mrs. Wilbur Douglass Jr., Barbara Hale, Mrs. Robert Lawson, Mrs. James Miller, and Mrs. John Walker, gathered around banquet table in Webster Hall  for bridge luncheon
